# Sofia Development Rules

## Documentation Parity

When planning any code change:
1. **Flag doc changes** alongside code changes in the plan
2. **Update docs** in the same commit/PR as code when possible
3. **CHANGELOG.md** must be updated for any user-facing change

### Development Workflow

```
1. User requests functionality
2. Discuss options
3. User approves option
4. AI creates plan with BOTH code AND doc changes flagged
5. Work through changes (code + docs together)
6. Mid-stream updates noted for both
7. Implementation loop
8. Approve code implementation
9. Doc review checkpoint (verify docs match new code)
10. Approve documentation
11. Release includes: new code, updated docs, changelog entry
```

### Documents to Check by Change Type

| Change Type | Check These Docs |
|-------------|------------------|
| New feature | README.md, relevant docs in documentation/, CHANGELOG.md |
| CLI change | documentation/sofia-*.md, CHANGELOG.md |
| Config change | documentation/sofia-monitor.md, .windsurf/ARCHITECTURE.md |
| Structure change | .windsurf/ARCHITECTURE.md, documentation/mx/*.md |
| Deprecation | CHANGELOG.md (with migration notes) |

### Plan Format

Every plan must include:
- [ ] Code changes (files, functions)
- [ ] Documentation changes (which docs, what sections)
- [ ] CHANGELOG entry (if user-facing)

### Doc Review Checkpoint

After code is approved, before final commit:
1. List all docs that were flagged for update
2. Verify each doc accurately reflects the new code
3. Check for stale references to old behavior
4. Confirm CHANGELOG entry is complete
5. Get explicit user approval for documentation

## Commit Protocol

- Code and related doc updates should be in the same commit when logical
- CHANGELOG updates can be batched at release time
- Always wait for explicit user approval before commit/push
- Never chain commit and push together; each requires separate approval

## Branch Strategy

- `main`: Development branch
- `public`: Release branch (GitHub default)
- Verify no private content before merging main → public
